metadata.name: Historical Pepes: Daniel Dinkum
metadata.description:
Daniel Dinkum (1888-2029) 

An Avant-Garde poet from Western Canada whose seminal work "Lilypad Requiem" laid the foundation for the Dadaist movement. 

"The is flower, red, red, Chrysler soul and a Ford heart, Machine, machine, machine" - Opening lines from Lilypad Requiem
